main event: A witness in Bakersfield, California reported seeing a slow-flying object with two very yellow-orange lights in August 1965.
interesting points: The witness was awakened by a loud noise, similar to a propeller-driven aircraft with adjustable pitch propellers.
The object was estimated to be at an altitude of 500 feet and flying at a speed of 125 knots.
The object had a highly luminous area that was 14 feet by 8 feet.
The Air Force responded that the sighting was likely an infrared photo solution or a high-altitude test aircraft.
The witness also reported seeing two other bright lights moving across the sky on September 1, 1955, which appeared to pulsate or grow dimmer and brighter as they moved.
sighted object: slow-flying object with two very yellow-orange lights
